race.comment: STREETCAR APOLLO (3) was denied by the barest of margins when resuming at Murray Bridge. Has returned in terrific order and is drawn to advantage for Toeroek, who sticks. Sure to be in this for a very long way. THERE GOES MY HERO (6) is knocking on the door and busting to break through. Drops back in trip off 29 days and will hope the early pace is genuine, so he can launch late. STOKOMO (2) chased gamely into second when resuming at Gawler. Fitter and will appreciate the rise in trip. ALL TOO MYSTI (8) proved too tough for them when scoring by a head here last time as favourite. Tougher this time but she's going too well to ignore. ANDREW'S MEMORY (7) broke through for a deserved win here last time when sticking his nose out on the line. Only needs to hold his form to be competitive.
